			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	-Marketing and Social Media Manager</p>
<p>
	We are immediately hiring a Marketing and Social Media Manager with a demonstrated record of creatively engaging the masses. You will launch and own all marketing initiatives around attracting and retaining an active user base for checkpoints.</p>
<p>
	You will come up with creative, headline grabbing promotions and be comfortable with quantifying which initiatives garner the strongest response. You will keep fresh and engaging contact on social media while engaging and responding to users. These can include contests, activities, user conversations that will help set the tone of our brand. In addition to promoting our own product, you will be integral to incorporating our advertisers in our marketing in a genuine way. These clients are world famous recognizable brands eager to connect to most customers via mobile.</p>
<p>
	You will take advantage of a ground level opportunity to create effective and smart campaigns that will turn heads in industries.</p>
<p>
	-How to Apply</p>
<p>
	Do your homework on us, our product, and existing social media. Send a personalized cover letter and resume for this position with links to previous social media work. This is extremely competitive position a top new mobile company. We want to know that you are excited about the opportunity and want to dive in.</p>
<p>
	Optional only if you want the job: Please develop tangible 2 marketing ideas that could be executed within social media alone (i.e. no app integration), and 2 that are more complex and can be tied to the app. Applications without a cover letter will be promptly eaten.</p>
<p>
	We have the relationships, leadership, and funding to create an unprecedented category of mobile advertising and we&rsquo;re looking forward to having you join us!<br />
	Skills</p>
<p>
	-Experience</p>
<p>
	You are a proven implementer with strong creative and copywriting skills. You are an already an expert in online marketing and have the portfolio to back it up. You have built large facebook and twitter followings (over several thousand). You crave a fast paced startup environment.</p>
<p>
	You have an unflappable demeanor and enjoy coming up with creative ideas, and proving their efficacy with facts.</p>
<p>
	You must be willing to embrace the life of a startup. This means the pride of ownership, the lack of bureaucracy, and the individual empowerment. This can also mean long hours to meet make or break deadlines. This includes the access to knocking on the CEO&rsquo;s office next door for clarification. Above all you should be excited about your work (life&rsquo;s too short not to be) and possess a willingness to trailblaze.&nbsp;</p>
